<subSubSection id="63812ECC0202C308FF26FDEADF88FD26" box="[132,232,630,656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2B247D470202C308FF26FDEADF88FD26" blockId="7.[132,776,630,720]" box="[132,232,630,656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">REMARKS</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="63812ECC0202C308FF26FD0ADB01FD67" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="2B247D470202C308FF26FD0ADB01FD67" blockId="7.[132,776,630,720]" lastBlockId="7.[810,1457,215,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FF26FD0ADE56FD07" authority="H. S. Lo" box="[132,310,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FF26FD0ADE56FD07" box="[132,310,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FDEEFD0ADC64FD18" authority="H. S. Lo" box="[588,772,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FDEEFD0ADC64FD18" box="[588,772,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by thecongested-cymose inflorescences,short peduncles, slenderly salverform corollas and subglobose capsules, but differs from the latter mainly by having erect stems (vs ascending), most plant parts glabrous or subglabrous (vs densely pubescent), leaf blades narrowly elliptic-oblong or elliptic-oblong(vs ovate to ovate-elliptic) and calyx lobes 
<quantity id="EC63D0A20202C308FC6AFECBDB4FFED9" box="[968,1071,343,369]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.7">1.7-3 mm</quantity>
long (vs 
<quantity id="EC63D0A20202C308FB25FECBDA62FED9" box="[1159,1282,343,370]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5-4.5 mm</quantity>
long) (
<bibRefCitation id="4F0A00B60202C308FAEBFECBDAC0FED9" author="LO H. S." box="[1353,1440,343,369]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="31 - 53" refId="ref2995" refString="LO H. S. 1986. - Materials for Chinese Rubiaceae (I). Bulletin of Botanical Research, Harbin 6 (4): 31 - 53." type="journal article" year="1986">Lo 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, there are five species of 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB10FEEBDA79FE39" authority="BLUME" box="[1202,1305,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB10FEEBDA79FE39" box="[1202,1305,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in northern 
<collectingCountry id="538C3DD70202C308FC2CFE0ADC88FE18" box="[910,1000,406,432]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4F0A00B60202C308FC51FE0BDB2AFE19" author="LO H. S." box="[1011,1098,407,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="86 - 110" refId="ref3026" refString="LO H. S. 1999. - Spiradiclis Blume, in LO H. S. (ed.), Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae. Vol. 71 (1). Science Press, Beijing: 86 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1999">Lo 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4F0A00B60202C308FBF6FE0BDBD2FE19" author="HO P. H." box="[1108,1202,407,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" refId="ref2901" refString="HO P. H. 2000. - An Illustrated Flora of Vietnam. Vol. 3. Tr e Publishing House, Ho Chi Minh City, 1020 p." type="book" year="2000">Hô 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4F0A00B60202C308FB1FFE0BDA2EFE19" author="LEE J. K. &amp; KHANG N. S. &amp; CHOUDHARY R. K. &amp; QUANG B. H." box="[1213,1358,406,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="645 - 651" refId="ref2932" refString="LEE J. K., KHANG N. S., CHOUDHARY R. K. &amp; QUANG B. H. 2019. - Two new records of Spiradiclis (Rubiaceae) from Vietnam. Korean Journal of Agricultural Science 46 (3): 645 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.7744 / kjoas. 20190051" type="journal article" year="2019">
Lee 
