). Among them, 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FCD0FE2ADB4FFE78" authority="H. S. Lo" box="[882,1071,438,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FCD0FE2ADB4FFE78" box="[882,1071,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB9CFE2BDBA7FE78" authority="Pit" box="[1086,1223,438,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptobotrya">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB9CFE2BDBA7FE78" box="[1086,1223,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. leptobotrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB5FFE2BDC29FE58" authority="H. S. Lo" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB5FFE2BDC29FE58" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to limestone karst areas and usually occur at elevations of 
<quantity id="EC63D0A20202C308FC17FE6ADB4DFDB9" box="[949,1069,502,529]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="450.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="300.0">300-600 m</quantity>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FBD4FE6BDB8EFDB8" authority="Blume" box="[1142,1262,503,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FBD4FE6BDB8EFDB8" box="[1142,1262,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FA80FE6BDAD0FDB8" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" box="[1314,1456,502,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FA80FE6BDAD0FDB8" box="[1314,1456,502,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grow on slightly acidic soil at elevations of 
<quantity id="EC63D0A20202C308FB4DFD8ADAE1FD99" box="[1263,1409,534,561]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="2700.0" valueMax="2900.0" valueMin="2500.0">2500-2900 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="EC63D0A20202C308FC8CFDAADCF9FDF9" box="[814,921,566,593]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="600.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="0.0">0-1200 m</quantity>
, respectively. Additionally, the flowering time of the genus in 
<collectingCountry id="538C3DD70202C308FC28FDCADC84FDD8" box="[906,996,598,624]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
is concentrated in May (
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB47FDCADA11FDD8" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" box="[1253,1393,598,624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB47FDCADA11FDD8" box="[1253,1393,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), July (
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FC97FDEADCF9FD38" authority="H. S. Lo" box="[821,921,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FC97FDEADCF9FD38" box="[821,921,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), September (
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB81FDEADBF5FD38" authority="Blume" box="[1059,1173,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB81FDEADBF5FD38" box="[1059,1173,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FB60FDEADA1CFD38" authority="H. S. Lo" box="[1218,1404,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FB60FDEADA1CFD38" box="[1218,1404,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and December (
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FC07FD0ADB49FD18" authority="Pit" box="[933,1065,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptobotrya">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FC07FD0ADB49FD18" box="[933,1065,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. leptobotrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). A key to the five species of 
<taxonomicName id="EC9B06C40202C308FAE8FD0ADAD0FD18" authority="Blume" box="[1354,1456,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="19EFA1550202C308FAE8FD0ADAD0FD18" box="[1354,1456,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="538C3DD70202C308FCE5FD29DCC1FD67" box="[839,929,693,719]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
is provided below.
